<H3> <TI>   Units Departing for `Southern Battlefield' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  94P20330A Split SLOBODNA DALMACIJA in Serbo-Croatian 9 Jan 
94 p II </F>

<F P=103> 94P20330A </F>
<F P=104>  Split SLOBODNA DALMACIJA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:CSO 

<F P=106> [Article by J. Bresan: "Company Travels to Position"] </F>
  [Text] Trogir--It is very lively every 10 days at the 
Trogir [a town near Split] railroad station. The reason is that 
members of the King Tomislav 2d Trogir Company of the 114th 
Brigade of the Croatian Army are leaving for positions on the 
southern battlefield. 
  Thus, we photographed the members of the 2d Trogir Company 
while they waited for the bus before their departure. They will 
replace their friends and fellow fighters, also members of the 
Trogir Company. 

</TEXT>

