<H3> <TI>   Nine-Member Constitutional Court Proposed </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  94P20312A Budapest MAGYAR NEMZET in Hungarian 18 Jan 94 p 5 </F>
<F P=103> 94P20312A </F>
<F P=104>  Budapest MAGYAR NEMZET </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hungarian </F>
Article Type:CSO 

<F P=106> [Unattributed article: "The Body's Recommendation: Instead </F>
of 15, Nine Constitutional Court Justices Are Enough"] 
  [Text] The Constitutional Court will soon introduce a 
legislative proposal in the National Assembly concerning the 
regulations that pertain to it. Concurrently with this, the 
Constitutional Court will initiate an amendment to the 
Constitution: the number of constitutional justices should be 
nine instead of 15. In connection with the information received 
by MTI, Laszlo Solyom, the chief justice of the Constitutional 
Court, disclosed that approval of the legislative proposal 
concerning the regulations and the requested amendment to the 
constitution are on the agenda for the 24 January meeting of the 
full Court. Answering a question, Laszlo Solyom said that in 
contrast to assertions appearing in the media, the 
Constitutional Court has not taken and is not taking any steps 
toward the election of a successor to Geza Herczegh, who 
resigned from his position as constitutional justice when he 
became a member of the International Court in The Hague. 

</TEXT>

