Varta, for instance, five batteries would be needed for 
permanent scheduled service with two busses between 6:00 a.m. 
and 10:00 p.m including the required battery exchange intervals. 
For the pilot projects, Neoplan and Varta are using led-traction 
batteries with tubular plates. 
  According to reports the Varta Perfect type battery with 
electrolyte circulation and Varta Aquamatik is very energy 
efficient and requires little maintenance. The charging time per 
battery is reported to be five to six hours. 
