<H3> <TI>   Italy: Science Park Projects for the South Launched </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MI0701150994 Milan IL SOLE-24 ORE in Italian 2 Dec 93 p 
15--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> MI0701150994 </F>
<F P=104>  Milan IL SOLE-24 ORE </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Italian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Naples. The science park projects will be launched 
by the end of January. The announcement was made by Aldo 
Romano, Science and Technology Park Committee Coordinator for 
the Ministry of Scientific Research, at a meeting held to 
commemorate the 70th anniversary of the CNR [National Research 
Council]. By the end of the year, the organizations whose 
proposals have been selected will be required to submit their 
general projects and the committee will see to launching the 
programs immediately after. 
  Ministry of Scientific and Technological Research 
Undersecretary Silvia Costa stated that the selection of 
organizations that had requested funding had been very severe 
and only 10 out of the 31 proposals presented have been 
considered "buildable" projects. Undersecretary Costa also 
explained that no facilities will be built to house the research 
and manufactuirng activities, but that there will be 
coordination among all the research institutes and companies 
connected with them. If projects that necessarily call for the 
construction of laboratories and plants are presented, these 
will be examined very carefully by the committee. 
  The Ministry for Extraordinary Interventions in Southern 
Italy had already allocated 1.1 trillion lire, 300 billion of 
which just for the start up phase. 

</TEXT>

